		<div id="div-comment-11282" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/9c9f168728f8e0e4b056bfb9b4d60a4b?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='http://omniweb.com/wordpress' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Joe</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-0-multisite-domain-mapping-tutorial/comment-page-11/#comment-11282">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2012-10-06T19:08:55+00:00">October 6, 2012 at 7:08 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>of course right after I post the question I *finally* figured out, the apache conf for the new site &#8216;x.my.domain.com&#8217; was rewriting to &#8216;my.domain.com&#8217;  &#8211; I updated the rewrite rule for the new site to rewrite to &#8216;x.my.domain.com&#8217; and all is well.  thanks for the great instructions!<br />
-Joe</p>
</div>

